Others: The Minnesota Twins aim to break their three-game home losing streak with a victory against the Atlanta Braves.
Marcell Ozuna leads the Braves with 63 extra base hits (26 doubles and 37 home runs). Ramon Laureano is 14-for-39 with two doubles, three home runs and six RBI over the past 10 games.
The Twins have gone 30-14 in games when they hit at least two home runs. The Braves have hit 173 total home runs to rank fourth in MLB play.
